The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Ondo State has described Lucky Ayedatiwa as the right choice of running mate for Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu. It described Ayedatiwa who hails from Ilaje local government in Ondo South as a grassroots politician that would add value to the party. State Chairman of the Ondo APC, Mr. Ade Adetimehin, who spoke in a telephone chat, said all stakeholders were in agreement on Ayedatiwa choice. Adetimehin said the issue of loyalty to the party was considered in picking Ayedatiwa. He urged all party members in the state to rally round Governor Akeredolu and his running mate to achieve victory at the polls. According to him, “It is APC in Ondo that met and took decision on who to pick as running mate. All the party organs and members are happy in the state. “Ayedatiwa is a grassroots politician that is very loyal to the party. We do not want anybody that will betray us in the future. With the emergence of Ayedatiwa as running mate from Ondo South, the victory of APC in October governorship election.”